dcterms:description: IMDB data is used for movie genre prediction, containing three node types: movie, actor, and director, along with two associations: movie-actor and movie-director. The movies are classified into three genres: action, comedy, and drama.
dcterms:title: IMDB

dcterms:description: ACM data is utilized for paper type prediction, featuring three node types: paper, author, and subject, with two associations: paper-author and paper-subject. The papers are classified into three areas: database, wireless communication, and data mining.

dcterms:description: DBLP data is used for author research area prediction, consisting of four node types: paper, author, conference, and term, with three associations: paper-author, paper-conference, and paper-term. Authors are classified into four research areas: database, data mining, artificial intelligence, and information retrieval.

dcterms:description: DrugADR data is used for drug adverse reaction prediction, containing drug-ADR pairs and five most frequent ADRs as class labels. The dataset includes drug similarity networks based on various similarities.
